11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201104063229/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/04/us/politics/election-trump-biden-recap.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=What will TV and social networks do if Trump prematurely declares victory?|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/11/02/media/tv-networks-election-night-victory/index.html|accessdate=2020-11-05|author=Business|first=Brian Stelter, CNN|work=CNN|archive-date=2021-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116102917/https://www.cnn.com/2020/11/02/media/tv-networks-election-night-victory/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>此外，前[[美國總統顧問|美國總統顧問]][[斯蒂芬·班農|史蒂夫·班农]]建议对[[安东尼·弗契|安东尼·福奇]]和联邦调查局局长[[克里斯托弗·A·雷|克里斯托弗·A·瓦雷]]“施加暴力”以此“警告联邦官员”为特朗普总统连任背书。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Steve Bannon Condemned, Banned From Twitter After Suggesting Violence As ‘A Warning To Federal Bureaucrats’|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/nicholasreimann/2020/11/05/steve-bannon-condemned-banned-from-twitter-after-suggesting-violence-as-a-warning-to-federal-bureaucrats/|accessdate=2020-11-06|author=Reimann|first=Nicholas|work=Forbes|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116100942/https://www.forbes.com/sites/nicholasreimann/2020/11/05/steve-bannon-condemned-banned-from-twitter-after-suggesting-violence-as-a-warning-to-federal-bureaucrats/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

